# Git Push After Every Task

When you finish any implementation, refactor, or fix in this repo:

1. **Always commit and push to `origin/main`** unless the user explicitly says not to push.
2. Do not leave completed work only on disk — the user deploys from GitHub via Coolify.
3. Push immediately after the change is verified (build passes when applicable).
4. Only skip push when the user says "don't push", "local only", or similar.

Default end-of-task flow: `git add` → `git commit` → `git push` → confirm clean status.
